About this hotel

Set in a colorful riad within the medina, this charming hotel is a 15-minute walk from shopping and entertainment at Jemaa el-Fnaa public square, and 1 km from the elaborate Bahia Palace.

Check-in time: 2:00 PM
Check-out time: 12:00 PM

From the airport it is easy to find. Use the bus 19 in front of the airport (behind the taxi area) for 30 DH per person to "Place Djemaa Al Fnaa" and walk the rest.
    One small disadvantage: The riad is located in the old town in a small subarea with only one entrance. The hotel is at the end of the street on the left side, you see a big sign above the way, easy to find. Anyways, there are a lot of people who try to rip of the guests from the different riads. They want to charge for show the correct riad or lye and say that the riad is closed and so on. Be careful, avoid to talk to street people.

    Medina

    Hammam bath houses and covered spice and textile souks line the maze of cobblestoned lanes in the Medina, which occupies Marrakesh’s original fortified citadel. At night, Jemaa el-Fna square teems with snake charmers, folk dancers, and street food vendors serving all manner of food. Bahia Palace and Le Jardin Secret are 19th-century complexes open to the public, with ornate courtyards, mosaics, and gardens.

    About this hotel

    Set in a colorful riad within the medina, this charming hotel is a 15-minute walk from shopping and entertainment at Jemaa el-Fnaa public square, and 1 km from the elaborate Bahia Palace. …

    The cozy rooms feature high ceilings and stained-glass windows, and open onto the courtyard. They also come with Wi-Fi, flat-screen TVs, sitting areas and safes. Room service is available.

    Breakfast is available. A casual restaurant on the roof terrace serves traditional Moroccan food. There's also a lounge with a fireplace, and a courtyard with sofas and a fountain. Massage treatments and car rentals are offered.
